commit f3a724d8105a79c9b59d1a14cce471b0c1852b39
Author: Niklas Vangerow <nikv@google.com>
Date:   Mon Jun 1 08:19:37 2026 -0700

    Consume memory space + core type in isGather instead of MemRefs.

    This change fixes several issues with mlir::tpu::isGather:

    * It moves the implementation to tpu_dialect.cc, which is a more natural
      place given the declaration site is tpu_dialect.h.
    * It changes the signature to take memory space + core type instead of
      MemRefType. Since no other part of the MemRefType is consumed, there's
      no reason to limit this utility to consuming whole MemRefTypes.
    * It updates the comment in the header to more accurately reflect what
      this function actually does. Importantly, it checks no property of the
      given `op`. `op` is merely used to attach a helpful error message in
      case both memory spaces are shared or local.

    PiperOrigin-RevId: 924720419
---
 jaxlib/mosaic/dialect/tpu/tpu_dialect.cc           | 27 ++++++++++++
 jaxlib/mosaic/dialect/tpu/tpu_dialect.h            |  9 ++--
 jaxlib/mosaic/dialect/tpu/tpu_ops.cc               | 50 +++++++++-------------
 .../dialect/tpu/tpu_ops_verification_test.cc       | 14 +++---
 4 files changed, 61 insertions(+), 39 deletions(-)

